text: Nizhniye Bishindy () is a rural locality (a selo) in Verkhnebishindinsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 744 as of 2010. There are 9 streets. == Geography == It is located 16 km from Tuymazy, 2 km from Verkhniye Bishindy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Nizhniye Bishindy
